            <div class="btx-container">
            <h1><span style="font-weight: 400;">Privacy policy</span></h1>
            <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Standard Privacy Policy for SixAds</span></p>
            <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Last Updated: 2018-09-28</span></p>
            <ol>
            <li><b> Confidentiality</b></li>
            </ol>
            <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">1.1 SixAds guarantees that personal and business data obtained from the app user (also referred to as data subject) and app user’s clients (store visitors) will never be disclosed to any third party except for our trusted data processors listed in 5.3. </span></p>
            <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">1.2 SixAds reserves the right to use the statistics collecte from running ads by SixAds app within SixAds ad network as well as other advertising means such as social networks (facebook, instagram), or search networks (google, bing, yahoo). This refers to but isn’t limited to collecting, analyzing, storing, aggregating and publishing data in a form of research and case studies.</span></p>
            <ol start="2">
            <li><b> Use of personal data</b></li>
            </ol>
            <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">2.1. SixAds uses the following personal data:</span></p>
            <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">User agent to render the ads properly</span></p>
            <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">IP for geo targeting and fraud control</span></p>
            <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Cookies to improve ad targeting based on browsing and purchase history. SixAds might also set their own tracking pixels from third parties such as facebook, google, instagram or others in order to drive targeted traffic to User’s store.</span></p>
            <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">2.2. SixAds reserves the right to store the above-mentioned data in its internal database as well as provide it to the 3rd party data processors listed in 5.3.</span></p>
            <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">2.3. The access to all the assets listed in 2.1 is to be provided by the data subject during the application onboarding process.</span></p>
            <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">2.4. Personal data is stored by SixAds during the whole period of the app usage and up to 1 year after the user chose to stop using SixAds services unless procedures listed in 4.2 and 6.5 are initiated.</span></p>
            <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">2.5 If the user chooses to transfer any personal data to SixAds, he/she guarantees that a proper consent for data collection, storage and transfer has been obtained from the data subjects.</span></p>
            <ol start="3">
            <li><b> Use of business data</b></li>
            </ol>
            <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">3.1. SixAds uses the following business data:</span></p>
            <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Store’s url, email, currency, products.</span></p>
            <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">3.2. SixAds reserves the right to store the above-mentioned data in its internal database as well as provide it to the 3rd party data processors listed in 5.3.</span></p>
            <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">3.3. Business data is stored by SixAds during the whole period of the app usage and up to 1 year after the user chose to stop using SixAds services unless procedures listed in 4.2 and 6.5 are initiated.</span></p>
            <ol start="4">
            <li><b> Consent for data use</b></li>
            </ol>
            <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">4.1. The data subject allows SixAds to process all the necessary personal and business data before creating a SixAds account.</span></p>
            <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">4.2. The data subject has the right to revoke the consent for data use at any time by uninstalling SixAds app. This will suggest an immediate termination of service SixAds provides as the data is vital for SixAds operation for reasons provided in 2.1 and 3.1.</span></p>
            <ol start="5">
            <li><b> Third-party data processors</b></li>
            </ol>
            <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">5.1. SixAds uses services of 3rd party data processors to make sure that the users are duly informed about all the aspects of the app operation.</span></p>
            <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">5.2. SixAds has made sure that the 3rd party data processors it cooperates with take data security very seriously and are compliant with all major data protection regulations, including </span><a href="https://www.eugdpr.org/eugdpr.org.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">GDPR</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span></p>
            <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">5.3. The following data processors may receive and store the personal and business data obtained from the data subject:</span></p>
            <ul>
            <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Amazon Web Services, Inc.</span></li>
            <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Intercom Inc.</span></li>
            <li>Facebook Inc.</li>
            </ul>
            <ol start="6">
            <li><b> Rights of the data subject</b></li>
            </ol>
            <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">6.1. The data subject has the right to:</span></p>
            <ul>
            <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">be duly informed about his/her personal data that is being processed by SixAds and 3rd party data processors</span></li>
            <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">request a digital copy of all the personal data SixAds has</span></li>
            <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">request a correction in the information SixAds processes if a discrepancy is found</span></li>
            <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">request a deletion of all the personal data that is being processed by SixAds and 3rd party data processors</span></li>
            </ul>
            <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">6.2. The information about the data processed is listed in Privacy Policy. The latest version of Privacy Policy. </span></p>
            <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">6.3. A digital copy of the personal data processed by SixAds and 3rd party data processors can be requested via e-mail support@sixads.com and shall be provided within 10 working days from the moment the request was received.</span></p>
            <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">6.4. A request for deletion of the personal data processed by SixAds and 3rd party data processors can be sent via e-mail support@sixads.com and shall be fulfilled within 10 working days from the moment the request was received.</span></p>
            <ol start="7">
            <li><b> Miscellaneous</b></li>
            </ol>
            <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">7.1. SixAds reserves the right to update the Privacy Policy without prior notice. Updated Privacy Policy comes into power once they are posted on this webpage. Your continued use of SixAds services automatically suggests your acceptance of the updated Privacy Policy. </span></p>
            <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">7.2. Any data-related questions are to be sent to support@sixads.com.</span></p>
            <p>&nbsp;</p>
            </div>
